<span id="freeTextContainer7524354692419707884">A non-fiction book discussing how forensic medicine came about in Manhattan from around the 1920s-1930s. The book is a great mix of science and history, telling the story of New York&apos;s first chief medical examiner, Charles Norris, and the toxicologist, Alexander Gettler. <br/><br/>The book uses a mix of poetic descriptions and scientific explanations, and a true-crime-esque writing style. Included is a lot of fascinating history and background into various poisons/toxins, their effects on the human body, </span>
  <span id="freeText7524354692419707884" style="display:none">A non-fiction book discussing how forensic medicine came about in Manhattan from around the 1920s-1930s. The book is a great mix of science and history, telling the story of New York's first chief medical examiner, Charles Norris, and the toxicologist, Alexander Gettler. <br /><br />The book uses a mix of poetic descriptions and scientific explanations, and a true-crime-esque writing style. Included is a lot of fascinating history and background into various poisons/toxins, their effects on the human body, cases in which they were used to murder people, and how the causes of death were determined.</span>
